Since 2008, DV has helped hundreds of Fortune 500 companies gain the most from their media spend by delivering best-in-class solutions across the digital ecosystem that help build a better industry. Learn more at doubleverify.com About The Role Do you like to build efficient data platforms, dealing with multiple constraints (volume, throttling, canonization, freshness, lineage) in a pragmatic way ? The mission of DoubleVerify Scibids is to provide media buyers with fully automated buying strategies for their campaigns, leading to unparalleled performances for a minimum of human work. The Data Engineering team is at the core of the Scibids products, and is responsible for communication between Scibids and its partners. We rely on a combination of open source and in-house solutions to provide accurate and reliable data. We ingest diverse and sometimes massive data streams. The team also manages outbound communications with partners: we leverage partner apis, cross-referenced with a set of business rules, to upload models generated by the Data Science teams. For example, in Q1 2025 we just finished integrating new data from Amazon and Google Ads (file ingestion, schema mapping, and API integration to push models and get configuration data). This role has a specific emphasis on tooling and automation, to support many initiatives, ranging from monitoring to CI/CD to auditing. As the rest of the Data Engineering team youâ€™ll be at the crossroads of many teams and will sometimes be coordinating their work. As Data Engineer, youâ€™ll be involved in a wide range of activities, including: - Core Data engineering tasks - Technical Project Coordination: Partner with infrastructure, data, and security teams to identify bottlenecks and build tailored automation solutions that enhance team efficiency and reduce manual work - Compliance & Security: Experience What we are looking for 0-2 years of experience in a technical or engineering support role, including personal projects or internships. Technical Skills Scripting: proficiency in Python (preferred) General SQL knowledge (we mostly use Mysql and BigQuery) Cloud Platforms: Familiarity with one of AWS, GCP, or Azure (we use Google) API Understanding: Basic understanding of REST APIs and their use in data integration. Workflow Orchestration: basic knowledge of (or ability to grasp) tools like Prefect, Airflow, GitHub Actions. Soft Skills Problem-Solving: A proactive attitude and the ability to investigate and resolve technical issues. Communication: Clear and concise written and verbal communication skills. Organization: Ability to manage multiple tasks and prioritize effectively. Learning Agility: A genuine desire to learn new technologies and adapt to changing priorities. Reporting to: Manager, Data Engineering Scibids offers a dynamic, inclusive environment where innovation and teamwork are celebrated.
